  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>

    <h3>Built-in Accessibility</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>The <code>&lt;summary&gt;</code> element receives automatic button-like keyboard behavior</li>
      <li>Screen readers announce the expanded/collapsed state</li>
      <li>Enter and Space keys toggle the state when summary is focused</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Best Practices</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Always include a <a href="/docs/elements/native/summary/"><code>&lt;summary&gt;</code></a> as the first child</li>
      <li>Keep summary text concise and descriptive</li>
      <li>Avoid nesting interactive elements inside <code>&lt;summary&gt;</code></li>
      <li>Ensure hidden content is not critical path information</li>
      <li>For multiple related panels, consider <code>&lt;accordion-wc&gt;</code> for keyboard arrow navigation between summaries</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Keyboard Support</h3>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Key</th>
          <th>Action</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><kbd>Enter</kbd></td>
          <td>Toggle open/closed when summary is focused</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><kbd>Space</kbd></td>
          <td>Toggle open/closed when summary is focused</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

